The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Cognizant buys UK firm
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Cognizant buys UK firm
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, May 10: Nasdaq-listed Cognizant has acquired London-based consulting firm PIPC Group for an undisclosed amount.        
	PIPC has more than 200 professionals, mainly in the UK, Australia, New Zealand, and the US. PIPCs programme management offerings will strengthen our ability to manage complex global projects, while expanding our geographic footprint, particularly in Australia, New Zealand and the UK, said Francisco DSouza, president and CEO of Cognizant.        
	IKF target        
	City-based IKF Technologies Ltd, which was on the prowl for a 100-seater BPO firm in the US, hopes to clinch a deal this quarter. We have shortlisted 23 companies. We aim to finalise at least one by the end of this quarter, CEO Mukesh Goyal told The Telegraph.                                                                                                                                                         
